President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday promised to rebuild all houses destroyed by the explosion that rocked Abule-Ado community in Amuwo-Odofin Local Government Area of Lagos on Sunday. This is even as emergency workers continued to search for the body of a missing person who may have died in the explosion. Daily Trust reports that about 20 persons lost their lives among who are students of Bethlehem Girl’s High School, while several houses were also destroyed in the early morning explosion that rocked the area. The Minister for Humanitarian Affairs, Disaster Management and Social Development, Sadiya Umar Farouq, who embarked on an on-the-spot assessment to the site, assured those affected by the explosion that the Federal Government would conduct a detailed Investigation to unravel the circumstances surrounding the unfortunate incident. The Minister who represented the President said the federal government will also partner with the state government to investigate the actual cause of the explosion. She described the explosion site as devastating, saying, “We are joining hands with the state government to support the victims of this incident. We are also going to work in the area of rebuilding these structures that has been destroyed by this incident,” she said. Lagos explosion kills principal, students, family of 4, many others Pressure mounts on Buhari to visit scene of Lagos explosion 2 killed, 80 houses, 30 cars destroyed in Lagos explosion